.:: Puzzle 5x4-Level-8-2::.
The people prefer 4 different music-genres: jazz, dubstep, r&b, folk
4 different games are played: canasta, chess, bridge, poker
There are 4 different favourite colors: brown, amber, aquamarine, blood-red
The people use 4 different means of transport: bike, subway, van, quad-bike
The people prefer 4 different types of sport: climbing, ice-hockey, cricket, rowing
 1. the person playing canasta is on the left or right of the fan of r&b##3
 2. the fan of dubstep is on the left or right of the person who's sport is ice-hockey##3
 3. the person who likes blood-red is not to the left of the person driving the subway##8
 4. the person who likes brown is between the person who likes amber and the person who likes aquamarine##2
 5. the person who likes brown is not the person who's sport is cricket##6
 6. the person playing bridge is somewhere to the left of the person who likes blood-red##5
 7. the person playing canasta is not to the right of the person who's sport is climbing##8
 8. the person driving the bike is somewhere to the left of the person who likes blood-red##5
 9. the person who likes brown is somewhere to the right of the person driving the bike##5
10. the person playing chess is in an odd position##4
11. the person driving the subway is on the right of the person who's sport is climbing##1
12. the person who's sport is cricket is not to the right of the person who's sport is climbing##8
13. the person driving the van is somewhere to the left of the person playing canasta##5
14. the person playing poker is the fan of folk##1
15. the person playing canasta is not to the left of the person driving the quad-bike##8
16. the person who's sport is climbing is not to the left of the person playing canasta##8
17. the person playing chess is the fan of dubstep##1
18. the fan of dubstep is not the person who likes amber##6
19. the fan of jazz is not the person playing bridge##6
20. the fan of folk is somewhere to the right of the person who likes brown##5
21. the person who likes amber is somewhere to the left of the person playing poker##5

.:: Answer ::.
