.:: Puzzle 5x4-Level-8-18::.
The people's birthday is in 4 different months: april, february, march, may
4 different games are played: scrabble, billiard, backgammon, poker
The people prefer 4 different types of sport: surfing, swimming, biathlon, skiing
4 different brands of cigars are smoked: alhambra, baccarat, bluemaster, ritmeester
The people have 4 different jobs:  designer, freelancer, pilot, social-worker
 1. the person who's sport is surfing is in an even position##4
 2. the person who's birthday is in may is in an odd position##4
 3. the person who's birthday is in february is somewhere between the pilot and the alhambra-smoker##7
 4. the person who's sport is swimming is between the social-worker and the person who's sport is skiing##2
 5. the person playing poker is in an odd position##4
 6. the designer is somewhere to the right of the baccarat-smoker##5
 7. the person who's birthday is in march is not to the left of the person who's birthday is in february##8
 8. the person who's birthday is in may is on the left of the person playing backgammon##1
 9. the person who's birthday is in april is not to the right of the person who's sport is swimming##8
10. the person who's birthday is in april is not the person who's sport is surfing##6
11. the designer is on the left or right of the person playing billiard##3
12. the bluemaster-smoker is the person who's sport is biathlon##1
13. the person who's birthday is in march is on the left or right of the person who's birthday is in april##3
14. the pilot is not to the right of the person playing poker##8
15. the person who's sport is biathlon is not to the left of the pilot##8
16. the alhambra-smoker is on the left or right of the person playing billiard##3
17. the person who's sport is swimming is not the ritmeester-smoker##6
18. the person playing billiard is on the left or right of the person who's sport is skiing##3
19. the person who's sport is biathlon is not to the right of the person who's sport is swimming##8
20. the person playing billiard is in an odd position##4

.:: Answer ::.
|               |     1      |      2      |    3     |     4      |
